---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Eniro — Pablo Anttila">
  <main>
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/work">← All work</a>
    </nav>

    <header>
      <small>2016–2017</small>
      <h1>Eniro</h1>
      <p>Online Sales MVP</p>
    </header>

    <figure>
      <p>[Project screenshot]</p>
    </figure>

    <article>
      <h2>What</h2>
      <p>Närvarokollen.se — a lead generation tool for Eniro's sales force. The portal aggregates data from multiple APIs to measure a business's online presence based on key contact information.</p>

      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>Frontend Developer working directly with stakeholders and product owner. Designed and developed the first iteration of the platform from scratch.</p>

      <h2>What I built</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>User journey</strong> — Wireframes and prototypes for the complete flow</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend app</strong> — REST API integration with JavaScript interface</li>
        <li><strong>WordPress plugin</strong> — Packaged the app with custom WooCommerce templates</li>
        <li><strong>Lead capture</strong> — User signup and data storage system</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>
        {['JavaScript', 'REST API', 'WordPress', 'WooCommerce', 'WP Engine'].map(tech => (
          <code>{tech}</code>
        ))}
      </p>

      <h2>Approach</h2>
      <p>Bootstrapped MVP approach — embedded in the marketing team to move fast. The goal was proving the concept quickly, then iterating based on real sales team feedback.</p>

      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>[Pablo: Add lead generation numbers, sales team adoption, or conversion data if available.]</p>
    </article>

    <nav>
      <a href="/work/tobii">← Tobii</a>
      <a href="/work/design-mobile">Design Mobile →</a>
    </nav>
  </main>
</Layout>
